Interface CharRange

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Presentable
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    CharRange.BoundRange, CharRange.UnboundRange

    public interface CharRange
extends Presentable
    Define, merge, and exclude ranges of Unicode characters.
    Author:
    Philippe Poulard

    • Nested Class Summary

      Nested Classes 
      Modifier and Type Interface and Description
      static class  CharRange.BoundRange
      A single interval with defined start and end boundaries.
      static interface  CharRange.Reversible
      Allow to specify a set of values in terms of inclusion or exclusion.
      static class  CharRange.UnboundRange
      Base implementation of unbound ranges.

    • Field Detail

      • CHAR_RANGE_COMPARATOR

        static final Comparator<CharRange> CHAR_RANGE_COMPARATOR
        Allow to compare ranges canonically. For example, !'b' and ['\u0000'-'a'] | ['c'-'\u10ffff'] are the same.
